\section*{Study of Assignment Problem and it’s Application.}

\section *{Introduction }
Introuction to proposed research topic:-\\    

   Assignment problem is degenerated form of transportation problem. Assignment problem,transportation problem are type of linear programming problem. Problems related to assignment have many applications such as transportation,healthcare,education,seating arrangement,business,sports etc. Assignment problem deals with allocation of varies resources to varies activityes on one to one correspondence. Assignment problem have two types\\
\begin{enumerate}
    \item Balanced Assignment Problem :- n objects are related to n objects.
    \item Unbalanced Assignment Problem:- n objects are related to m objects.
\end{enumerate}
 \\   


\section*{Definition and Mathematical Formulation of  general assignment problem :}\\

The general aim of Assignment problem is to optimize the allocation of  resources to demand points where both resources and demand point share equal number. Therefore assignment problem can be presented as :\\

	Optimize\\   
$\sum_{i=1}^{n} $   % Summation: Sum of x_i from i=1 to n
$\sum_{j=1}^{n} $   % Summation: Sum of x_j from j=1 to n
c_{ij} x_{ij} <re
 ……..(1)\\
 
	Subject to
 
$\sum_{i=1}^{n} x_{ij}$   % Summation: Sum of x_i from i=1 to n
    = 1    		                      i=1,2,3…,n ……(2)\\
    
$\sum_{i=1}^{n} x_{ij}$   % Summation: Sum of x_i from i=1 to n    
			 =1                           j=1,2,3…n ……(3)\\
    
x_{ij}	
	 = 0 or 1,   i=1,2,…n          j=1,2…n     ……..…(4)\\

  
  which are  is the cost or efectiveness of assignment resource to   demand,  is 0 or 1 as presented in equation (4) and n is number of resources or demands. The constraints of problem are defined as equation (2) and (3). Equation (2) indicates that each resource i  needs to be assigned to one demand j, while(3) show that each demand  j needs to be assigned to only one resource i.[2]

\section*{Solution method :-}
	The assignment problem can be solved by the following four methods :
\begin{enumerate}
    \item Enumeration Method
    \item Simplex Method
    \item Trasportation Method
    \item Hungarian Method
\end{enumerate} \\

Now a days mathematicians found new techniques to solve assignment problem which are as follows :\\  

\section*{*Heuristics algorithm} \\		
\begin{enumerate}
                                 \item Constructed method
                                 \item Limited enumeration method
                                 \item Improvement method
                                 \item Simulated annealing technique
                                 \item Genetic algorithms
\end{enumerate}\\

\section*{*Metaheuristic algorithm :-}
\begin{enumerate}
                                 \item Local search algorithm
                                 \item Population search algorithm
\end{enumerate}\\

